{"tid":2389004,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"藍營代表梁燕城博士講英文俾人笑垃圾","createTime":"2021-01-31T14:12:40.000Z","updateTime":"2021-01-31T15:41:23.000Z","uid":76657,"like":5,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"e515086678d3854055abd402958f04a98fe52d06","tid":2389004,"uid":76657,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:12:40.000Z","msg":"【學英文】吳若琦：//「比何君堯的爛英文更爛」- 馮睎乾這樣形容梁燕城博士為了證明何君堯的清白， 以中國文化專家身份，給英國事務律師紀律審裁處遞交的那份英文供詞。<br />\n<br />\n梁博士似乎沒覺得他的英文很爛， 因他驕傲地把那份供詞發到他的臉書，並標榜自己是「唐君毅和牟宗三的學生，且發表過一百多篇學術論文。」<br />\n<br />\n我抽出他所寫的其中一段英文，作出以下點評：<br />\n<br />\n梁博士原文：<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;When people speak in this phrase 殺無赦 (sha wu she) nowadays, its meaning is for a dramatic  expression only. From the point of modern day ordinary language analysis, the meaning of 殺無赦 (sha wu she) is &ldquo;unforgiven&rdquo; and not really mean &ldquo;killing&rdquo;. One of the example is a Hollywood movie namely &ldquo;Unforgiven&rdquo; in 1992, directed by Clint Eastwood and written by David Peoples, its Chinese title in Chinese translation as 殺無赦 (sha wu she) in Taiwan. Therefore, the way of using this phrase nowadays is to proof more on to signify meaning of unforgiven instead of killing.&rdquo;//"},{"pid":"c27bf42e6abc9f992d41a12e5db3e70401990dbf","tid":2389004,"uid":76657,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:13:47.000Z","msg":"To proof個到真係<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c51ffeb589d0b28bbf7775b66198f2dea51f040f","tid":2389004,"uid":142763,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"e515086678d3854055abd402958f04a98fe52d06","tid":2389004,"uid":76657,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:12:40.000Z","msg":"【學英文】吳若琦：//「比何君堯的爛英文更爛」- 馮睎乾這樣形容梁燕城博士為了證明何君堯的清白， 以中國文化專家身份，給英國事務律師紀律審裁處遞交的那份英文供詞。<br />\n<br />\n梁博士似乎沒覺得他的英文很爛， 因他驕傲地把那份供詞發到他的臉書，並標榜自己是「唐君毅和牟宗三的學生，且發表過一百多篇學術論文。」<br />\n<br />\n我抽出他所寫的其中一段英文，作出以下點評：<br />\n<br />\n梁博士原文：<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;When people speak in this phrase 殺無赦 (sha wu she) nowadays, its meaning is for a dramatic  expression only. From the point of modern day ordinary language analysis, the meaning of 殺無赦 (sha wu she) is &ldquo;unforgiven&rdquo; and not really mean &ldquo;killing&rdquo;. One of the example is a Hollywood movie namely &ldquo;Unforgiven&rdquo; in 1992, directed by Clint Eastwood and written by David Peoples, its Chinese title in Chinese translation as 殺無赦 (sha wu she) in Taiwan. Therefore, the way of using this phrase nowadays is to proof more on to signify meaning of unforgiven instead of killing.&rdquo;//"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:15:28.000Z","msg":"Namely??? Wtf"},{"pid":"2ac5b152480531d82b443a668912ff2760b43e65","tid":2389004,"uid":62176,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:16:18.000Z","msg":"連我都睇得明又真係差左啲<img src=\"/assets/faces/mouse/notcry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"41ff01785a56406bc515c6239bf8237e37305afa","tid":2389004,"uid":51271,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:17:10.000Z","msg":"英國律師委員會又受，吹脹"},{"pid":"fef05f6fcece690430ebcfa24aa84129008643f4","tid":2389004,"uid":50144,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"2ac5b152480531d82b443a668912ff2760b43e65","tid":2389004,"uid":62176,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:16:18.000Z","msg":"連我都睇得明又真係差左啲<img src=\"/assets/faces/mouse/notcry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:17:26.000Z","msg":"但佢錯呢&hellip;&hellip;"},{"pid":"d1a0071287376bfa66a172bdfa28c8ffa3ae5a57","tid":2389004,"uid":76657,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-31T14:20:20.000Z","msg":"咁撚廢都做到博士<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />搏命食屎就有份"},{"pid":"9fb62c52b7c67f840f122074477f5f182f661aa1","tid":2389004,"uid":76657,"lik